cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.MA, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the challenges of engineering collective adaptive systems, which often involve distributed computing. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses the resiliency properties of collective adaptive systems, which are often related to control theory. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper discusses the implementation details of collective adaptive systems. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a relevant category as the paper discusses the behaviour of collectives, which can be seen as a type of multiagent system. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also relevant as the paper discusses the functional computational model used in aggregate computing, which can be seen as a type of AI.
